messageBody:
peter_r_guinness scripsit:

> File : /International Quikscript/Malt's International Quikscript Project/Intro and Notes.pdf
> Uploaded by : peter_r_guinness <malt99@...>

I think this is an excellent proposal. A few points:

In the four cases NEAR, CURE, FIRE, SHOWER you've decided whether to put
in an Utter or not based on ease of writing, which is reasonable given
Quikscript's purposes. It's more or less an arbitrary choice: I would
have gone without an Utter in NEAR, CURE and with one in FIRE, SHOWER.

It's worth adding some examples to rule 31 that don't involve "ew",
such as tune, dune, lute.

I haven't been able to look at the spreadsheet yet. Is it posted?

--
